########## INSTALLATION MANUAL

## For sinQC (used in script-sc.py):

- Install R, Python, and in R:

install.packages(gplots)
install.packages(ROCR)
library(gplots)
library(ROCR)

- Then in the terminal:

tar -xvf SINQC_v1.5

## For RSEM (used in script-sc.py):

- Install R, Python, C++, Perl (also Bowtie2 if not already installed)

- Then in the terminal:

tar -xvf RSEM-1.3.0.tar
cd RSEM-1.3.0
make

## For HTseq:

Go to the corresponding folder
In terminal:
python setup.py build
python setup.py —-user

########## STARTING THE PIPELINE

## script.py:
Your file is named “file” and “mode” is either PE or SE (modify in Python file)

In BASH shell: python script.py

## script-sc.py:
Your file is named “file” and “mode” is either PE or SE (modify in Python file)

In BASH shell: python script-sc.py

See script[-sc]_multiple to start a several-file analysis
